{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_019akfsj2Y8SQKTqVDD9qG21","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Access denied via Graph API. The Azure CLI token doesn't have the necessary SharePoint permissions to access this content storage container.\n\nLet me try the Loop API directly with a proper token, since the Loop MCP server might construct the pageId differently.\n\nActually, let me go back to the Loop API approach. The MCP server returned 404, but maybe the encoding is slightly off. Let me check if the `H` vs `G` difference matters. The driveId from the nav has `MH9F` while the workspace one has `MG9F`. These are URL-safe base64 encoded GUIDs and they're different drives.\n\nActually wait - I wonder if the issue is that the driveId `b!lRZQfeTZQ0C9IoRwG5pqAiArSWyR8NpBioqVzLj3MH9F` contains characters that need different encoding in the pageId. \n\nLooking more closely at the full driveId string and how I'm constructing the pageId for base64 encoding — I'm using the domain and the driveId prefix, but I might be truncating it incorrectly when building the encoded value.\n\nLet me try hitting the Loop API directly instead of going through the MCP wrapper to see if that gives me a clearer error, or test the LWS API with the token to narrow down where the issue is.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":904,"cache_read_input_tokens":47250,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":904,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"global"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4004397f-9402-4049-ba0c-52ed9b7104fc","uuid":"352e6997-203b-42ec-95a8-3c15f8840aee"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_019akfsj2Y8SQKTqVDD9qG21","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01TXJmh3aYnhbirwKNMyxJzd","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"node -e \"\nconst https = require('https');\nconst { execSync } = require('child_process');\nconst token = execSync('az account get-access-token --resource https://api.loop.cloud.microsoft --query accessToken -o tsv', {encoding:'utf8'}).trim();\n\nconst domain = 'microsoft.sharepoint-df.com';\nconst driveId = 'b!lRZQfeTZQ0C9IoRwG5pqAiArSWyR8NpBioqVzLj3MH9F-3RQf0crQokI7f1IpihS';\nconst itemId = '01KXJWT5Z5K3AN367SSJFKWTYQOJM3A37I';\nconst pageId = Buffer.from(domain + ',' + driveId + ',' + itemId).toString('base64');\nconsole.log('pageId:', pageId);\n\nconst postData = JSON.stringify({options: {type: 'markdown'}});\nconst opts = {\n  hostname: 'prod.api.loop.cloud.microsoft',\n  path: '/v0.1/pages/' + encodeURIComponent(pageId),\n  method: 'POST',\n  headers: {\n    'Authorization': 'Bearer ' + token,\n    'Content-Type': 'application/json',\n    'Content-Length': Buffer.byteLength(postData),\n    'MS-CV': require('crypto').randomUUID()\n  }\n};\nconst req = https.request(opts, (res) => {\n  let data = '';\n  res.on('data', c => data += c);\n  res.on('end', () => {\n    console.log('Status:', res.statusCode);\n    if (res.statusCode === 200) {\n      const parsed = JSON.parse(data);\n      console.log('Title:', parsed.title);\n      console.log('Content:', parsed.content?.substring(0, 8000));\n    } else {\n      console.log(data.substring(0, 2000));\n    }\n  });\n});\nreq.write(postData);\nreq.end();\n\" 2>&1","description":"Fetch Loop page via LWS API directly","timeout":30000},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":904,"cache_read_input_tokens":47250,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":904,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8,"ser